node.text:
When I was 19, I was bitten by a radioactive spider...

I’m joking, but I did nearly die though. 

[Please enjoy this short cinematic visual of my backstory: the true origin story of ‘The Samurider’.]

“When I was 19, I had a serious motorbike accident; I was cut off by a van suddenly turning. I crashed straight into it and nose-dived 20ft through the air before landing on my face. I broke my neck and my right hand and lost my memory for a while. (most of it did come back eventually).

A couple days later, my bf broke up with me. Days after that, I lost my job as a regional sales executive for a huge tech brand. And for the first time in my life, I hit rock-bottom and fell into depression.

I thought it was the worst thing to ever happen to me... but rock-bottom was the solid foundation that I needed to rebuild my life.

I was bed-bound, so I did nothing for weeks but watch anime and feel sorry for myself. I watched SO MUCH anime. Mostly Naruto. (if you like anime, you’ll know how inspiring and motivating it can be.) So eventually I had the idea, that if my heroes could always overcome their ridiculously-chaotic adversity and become even stronger, then why couldn’t I?

Well, I really needed a hero, so I decided to try my luck at becoming one: and that’s how The Samurider came to be and became my superhero alter-ego.

I started going to the gym, with a vengeance. Not just for strength and aesthetics, but with the intention of training myself to become a master of antipersonnel tactics and sabotage.. but I still had my wrist in a cast, so I started with the basics. Then I started teaching myself martial arts from videos I found on YouTube.

As I began to change on the inside, the outside of me changed too: and I got rid of my eurocentricly-styled weaves/wigs and chose to wear my natural hair proudly as the crown that it is.

A few months later, on my 21st birthday, I got a tattoo: the ‘Will of Fire’ symbol from Naruto tattooed onto my solar plexus. (I put it on my solar plexus to mentally “seal” away the pain of my chronic anxiety), and so I promised myself 3 things from that day onwards:

node.text:
“The warrior of light needs time to herself.
And she uses that time for rest, contemplation and to contact the Soul of the World. Even in the midst of battle, she manages to meditate.”

The warrior knows that the most powerful weapon she can be is an instrument of peace. She knows that in the silence of her heart, she will hear an order that will guide her. 

Even in the chaoses of life, we all have the capacity to stand in the centre of our own peace. 

-

If you want to conquer the anxiety of life, live in the moment. Live in the breath.

For a moment, just breathe, as I share 60 seconds of my peace with you.

#sundayserenity
